00:33:50,832 --> 00:33:56,112
♪Too afraid to face tomorrow♪

593
00:33:58,640 --> 00:34:03,689
♪Perhaps wander aimlessly♪

594
00:34:05,136 --> 00:34:10,726
♪Forgive my silence♪

595
00:34:12,912 --> 00:34:18,744
♪Green grass,
distant hills, setting moon♪

596
00:34:20,272 --> 00:34:22,448
♪Don't wait for me.♪

597
00:34:53,040 --> 00:34:58,728
♪If you were by my side♪

598
00:35:00,627 --> 00:35:06,171
♪That'd be my greatest wish♪

599
00:35:07,984 --> 00:35:10,199
♪Don't wait for me♪

600
00:35:10,199 --> 00:35:10,960
That monster.

601
00:35:12,519 --> 00:35:13,519
You're his daughter.

602
00:35:13,519 --> 00:35:14,440
How can he do that?

603
00:35:15,119 --> 00:35:16,079
He resents my mom.

604
00:35:18,320 --> 00:35:19,840
He said she was promiscuous

605
00:35:19,840 --> 00:35:20,679
and seduced men.

606
00:35:22,599 --> 00:35:23,519
Still want fish cakes?

607
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:24,639
It's too far.

608
00:35:25,400 --> 00:35:28,320
I will make tomato egg noodles tonight.

609
00:35:29,320 --> 00:35:30,639
Your mom will be back soon.

610
00:35:36,079 --> 00:35:36,599
Mom.

611
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:56,800
Ye.

612
00:35:57,079 --> 00:35:58,239
Why are you home today?

613
00:35:58,599 --> 00:35:59,440
Day off today.

614
00:35:59,440 --> 00:36:00,239
Coming back to cook.

615
00:36:01,480 --> 00:36:02,280
Go ahead.

616
00:36:02,719 --> 00:36:03,079
Alright.

617
00:36:11,119 --> 00:36:11,920
Where are you going?

618
00:36:12,360 --> 00:36:13,719
Explain yourself today!

619
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:18,159
You sold yourself
for a can of malted milk?

620
00:36:18,480 --> 00:36:18,920
Mom.

621
00:36:18,920 --> 00:36:19,960
Bo.

622
00:36:20,320 --> 00:36:21,679
What are you doing now?

623
00:36:21,679 --> 00:36:22,960
Mom, stay out of this!

624
00:36:23,719 --> 00:36:24,519
Speak clearly!

625
00:36:24,599 --> 00:36:24,960
Tang.

626
00:36:25,239 --> 00:36:25,880
Mom!

627
00:36:25,880 --> 00:36:26,760
Let's go.

628
00:36:26,920 --> 00:36:27,719
Mom!

629
00:36:28,039 --> 00:36:29,239
I saw it today.

630
00:36:29,559 --> 00:36:31,559
You got out of his car
at the alley entrance.

631
00:36:31,559 --> 00:36:32,880
Have you no shame?

632
00:36:33,320 --> 00:36:35,039
All for a can of malted milk?

633
00:36:35,280 --> 00:36:36,840
Ye Yibo, stop talking nonsense.

634
00:36:37,199 --> 00:36:38,920
We're just ordinary friends.

635
00:36:39,599 --> 00:36:41,400
He gave me this just to show

636
00:36:41,400 --> 00:36:42,079
his gratitude.

637
00:36:42,079 --> 00:36:42,719
Mom!

638
00:36:43,159 --> 00:36:43,920
Was it that man?

639
00:36:44,840 --> 00:36:45,639
The malted one?

640
00:36:46,880 --> 00:36:47,480
Is it him?

641
00:36:47,480 --> 00:36:49,079
Ye Yibo, stop talking nonsense!

642
00:36:49,079 --> 00:36:50,000
Out with it!

643
00:36:53,679 --> 00:36:54,840
Mom, I'm home.

644
00:36:55,239 --> 00:36:56,039
Give me your dress.

645
00:36:56,920 --> 00:36:57,719
Who paid for it?

646
00:36:58,159 --> 00:36:58,760
I bought it.

647
00:36:59,400 --> 00:37:00,960
But I've never seen it.

648
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:03,280
I bought it.

649
00:37:03,559 --> 00:37:05,239
Where did you get the money to buy this?

650
00:37:06,159 --> 00:37:07,360
Who gave you the money?

651
00:37:08,119 --> 00:37:09,400
Who paid for this?

652
00:37:10,400 --> 00:37:11,239
Who?

653
00:37:11,559 --> 00:37:12,559
I saved it myself.

654
00:37:12,559 --> 00:37:13,400
Mom.

655
00:37:13,599 --> 00:37:15,199
You seduced another man, right?

656
00:37:15,199 --> 00:37:16,199
Who did you seduce?

657
00:37:16,440 --> 00:37:16,920
Get inside!

658
00:37:16,920 --> 00:37:17,519
Mom!

659
00:37:19,679 --> 00:37:20,360
Explain yourself!

660
00:37:20,360 --> 00:37:21,079
Go out with me.

661
00:37:21,079 --> 00:37:21,760
Go, hurry.

662
00:37:21,760 --> 00:37:23,159
Which man did you seduce this time?

663
00:37:23,199 --> 00:37:24,079
I didn't.

664
00:37:24,079 --> 00:37:24,559
Go.

665
00:37:24,760 --> 00:37:25,519
Mom.

666
00:37:25,519 --> 00:37:26,280
You didn't?

667
00:37:26,920 --> 00:37:28,400
My mom wasn't that kind of person.

668
00:37:29,119 --> 00:37:30,239
He's the mentally ill one.

669
00:37:31,159 --> 00:37:32,719
Whenever my mom spoke to other men,

670
00:37:32,719 --> 00:37:33,760
he'd fly into rage.

671
00:37:34,239 --> 00:37:35,639
Later, he gambled.

672
00:37:37,039 --> 00:37:37,639
When he lost,

673
00:37:38,119 --> 00:37:40,199
he'd come home
and beat my mom even worse

674
00:37:41,679 --> 00:37:42,960
until she couldn't bear it

675
00:37:43,880 --> 00:37:45,039
and ran away from home.

676
00:37:45,800 --> 00:37:46,760
He couldn't find her,

677
00:37:48,599 --> 00:37:50,079
so he took his anger out on me.

678
00:37:50,519 --> 00:37:52,039
Didn't the factory leaders intervene?

679
00:37:53,079 --> 00:37:53,760
Didn't you

680
00:37:53,760 --> 00:37:55,119
think about talking to them?

681
00:37:58,360 --> 00:37:59,599
They worked at the same place.

682
00:38:01,960 --> 00:38:03,199
My mom was the cashier.

683
00:38:04,199 --> 00:38:05,880
She took the factory funds
when she left.

684
00:38:08,599 --> 00:38:09,519
Ye Yibo cried and said

685
00:38:09,519 --> 00:38:10,840
he'd repay this money.

686
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:13,400
The factory leaders were moved.

687
00:38:13,880 --> 00:38:15,559
Tang, it's still hot.

688
00:38:15,559 --> 00:38:16,559
Wait for it to cool down.

689
00:38:19,559 --> 00:38:20,599
I don't mind,

690
00:38:20,599 --> 00:38:21,760
but she needs to eat.

691
00:38:23,440 --> 00:38:24,039
Ye.

692
00:38:25,639 --> 00:38:27,519
This isn't a small amount of money.

693
00:38:28,039 --> 00:38:28,679
Director Wei,

694
00:38:28,679 --> 00:38:29,840
I'll repay this money.

695
00:38:29,840 --> 00:38:31,360
I've discussed it with Secretary Liu.

696
00:38:31,840 --> 00:38:33,719
I'll write an IOU.

697
00:38:33,719 --> 00:38:35,280
Deduct it from my wages later.

698
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:36,360
I won't default.

699
00:38:36,519 --> 00:38:38,480
Then how will you and your family eat?

700
00:38:38,599 --> 00:38:39,239
No, I...

701
00:38:39,559 --> 00:38:41,039
I can manage the hardships.

702
00:38:41,320 --> 00:38:43,039
Tang and I eat simply.

703
00:38:43,599 --> 00:38:44,679
Just let me keep a little

704
00:38:45,039 --> 00:38:46,800
for my mom's medical bills.

705
00:38:49,920 --> 00:38:52,679
There's been no news
of Wu Fengying at all?

706
00:38:53,039 --> 00:38:54,480
Her hometown relatives are all gone.

707
00:38:54,840 --> 00:38:57,159
I don't know where to look for her.

708
00:38:57,559 --> 00:38:58,159
How about this?

709
00:38:58,320 --> 00:38:59,320
Write me an IOU.

710
00:39:00,159 --> 00:39:01,719
If you can repay the money,

711
00:39:02,119 --> 00:39:03,599
the factory won't press charges.

712
00:39:05,639 --> 00:39:07,639
Director Wei,
I'll definitely repay this.

713
00:39:08,199 --> 00:39:09,800
I'll come to your office tomorrow.

714
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:10,360
Thank you.

715
00:39:11,119 --> 00:39:12,079
I'll be going.

716
00:39:12,360 --> 00:39:13,320
Take care of the child.

717
00:39:14,440 --> 00:39:15,000
Goodbye, Ye.

718
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:15,679
Take care.

719
00:39:49,840 --> 00:39:51,599
He never spoke ill of my mom

720
00:39:51,599 --> 00:39:53,239
in front of others.

721
00:39:54,119 --> 00:39:56,159
He always said it was his poverty

722
00:39:57,440 --> 00:39:58,920
that made her suffer so much.

723
00:40:01,280 --> 00:40:02,400
All these years, everyone

724
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:03,440
saw him repaying

725
00:40:04,519 --> 00:40:06,880
the debts, raising me through hardships,

726
00:40:07,239 --> 00:40:09,559
and caring for
my grandma in the hospital.

727
00:40:12,320 --> 00:40:14,360
When the sugar factory caught fire,

728
00:40:16,280 --> 00:40:17,719
he rushed into the flames alone,

729
00:40:17,719 --> 00:40:18,920
saving over a dozen people.

730
00:40:19,159 --> 00:40:21,800
The factory paraded in with an award.

731
00:40:23,039 --> 00:40:24,119
He stood in the hall,

732
00:40:24,119 --> 00:40:25,199
wearing a red flower,

733
00:40:25,199 --> 00:40:26,920
solemnly vowing to be

734
00:40:26,920 --> 00:40:27,960
a just and courageous man.

735
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:32,519
Whenever my neighbors needed help,

736
00:40:32,519 --> 00:40:33,360
if he was home,

737
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:34,360
he'd assist them.

738
00:40:35,679 --> 00:40:37,199
Those who tried matchmaking for him

739
00:40:37,199 --> 00:40:38,280
all got turned down.

740
00:40:38,840 --> 00:40:40,360
He said he'd not let me be mistreated

741
00:40:40,679 --> 00:40:41,440
by a stepmother.

742
00:40:43,639 --> 00:40:45,599
I told people Ye Yibo was a bad person.

743
00:40:46,480 --> 00:40:47,280
Who'd believe that?

744
00:40:56,119 --> 00:40:57,360
Scum.

745
00:40:58,639 --> 00:41:00,360
Worse than an animal.

746
00:41:03,880 --> 00:41:05,519
Every time I fought back,

747
00:41:06,559 --> 00:41:08,639
it only made things worse for me.

748
00:41:10,159 --> 00:41:11,920
I ran out and told people many times,

749
00:41:11,920 --> 00:41:14,079
but he always claimed
I was mentally ill.

750
00:41:15,079 --> 00:41:16,480
He even consulted doctors

751
00:41:16,480 --> 00:41:17,679
and learned a term called

752
00:41:17,679 --> 00:41:18,840
delusional disorder.

753
00:41:19,360 --> 00:41:20,760
Everyone said my mom ran away.

754
00:41:21,199 --> 00:41:22,039
I was insane.

755
00:41:27,440 --> 00:41:28,239
Since childhood,

756
00:41:28,719 --> 00:41:29,840
I've never seen my father.

757
00:41:32,760 --> 00:41:34,280
My mom told me then

758
00:41:36,079 --> 00:41:36,960
she'd go find my dad

759
00:41:37,960 --> 00:41:39,519
and come get me when she found him.

760
00:41:41,719 --> 00:41:42,800
But after that day,

761
00:41:44,800 --> 00:41:45,960
I never saw her again.

762
00:41:47,079 --> 00:41:49,039
I was only 4 years old then.

763
00:41:52,480 --> 00:41:54,280
I was in our house,

764
00:41:55,400 --> 00:41:56,480
nearly starving to death.

765
00:41:59,559 --> 00:42:00,719
Then I went out

766
00:42:03,280 --> 00:42:04,679
to scavenge food from trash bins.

767
00:42:13,119 --> 00:42:13,960
Later on,

768
00:42:14,719 --> 00:42:15,880
I got sent to an orphanage.

769
00:42:20,440 --> 00:42:22,360
My parents left me nothing.

770
00:42:27,599 --> 00:42:28,599
Not even a proper name.

771
00:42:29,960 --> 00:42:31,199
I only knew myself as Xun.

772
00:42:34,159 --> 00:42:35,559
My current name

773
00:42:37,079 --> 00:42:38,960
was given by Chubby Auntie
at the orphanage.

774
00:42:45,760 --> 00:42:48,039
Chubby Auntie is Miss Tan's mother.

775
00:42:51,719 --> 00:42:53,159
That was when I realized

776
00:42:54,360 --> 00:42:55,639
my birth parents

777
00:42:57,840 --> 00:42:59,159
never cared about me at all.

778
00:43:00,559 --> 00:43:02,039
So whether I become a wolf

779
00:43:03,280 --> 00:43:04,199
or a dog,

780
00:43:05,159 --> 00:43:06,519
I have to survive.

781
00:43:09,519 --> 00:43:11,559
Did you ever go back to search?

782
00:43:12,519 --> 00:43:14,639
Maybe your mom
came back looking for you?

783
00:43:15,119 --> 00:43:16,199
Of course I went back.

784
00:43:18,800 --> 00:43:20,440
But the old house had collapsed.

785
00:43:21,960 --> 00:43:23,400
She never came back at all.

786
00:43:25,960 --> 00:43:27,519
Without Chubby Auntie,

787
00:43:29,519 --> 00:43:30,736
I would have starved to death.

788
00:43:32,519 --> 00:43:34,559
No wonder Miss Tan
worries about you so much.

789
00:43:39,639 --> 00:43:41,119
Both Miss Tan and Chubby Auntie

790
00:43:42,039 --> 00:43:43,320
have always told me

791
00:43:43,800 --> 00:43:44,960
to study hard

792
00:43:45,519 --> 00:43:46,599
and gain more knowledge,

793
00:43:47,880 --> 00:43:49,239
so I could succeed in the future.

794
00:43:51,519 --> 00:43:52,719
But I did study hard.

795
00:43:55,480 --> 00:43:56,920
My classmates all looked down on me.

796
00:43:58,719 --> 00:43:59,880
They called me a stray dog

797
00:44:00,480 --> 00:44:02,840
and threw my books in the toilet.

798
00:44:04,280 --> 00:44:05,039
I couldn't take it,

799
00:44:05,760 --> 00:44:06,480
so I fought back.

800
00:44:09,639 --> 00:44:12,280
Then I got sent to reform school.

801
00:44:14,480 --> 00:44:16,079
Xin never gave up on me.

802
00:44:18,239 --> 00:44:18,920
Through her,

803
00:44:18,920 --> 00:44:20,280
I met Cha.

804
00:44:21,360 --> 00:44:22,719
But Xin always thought

805
00:44:22,880 --> 00:44:24,119
Cha was a bad influence.

806
00:44:26,039 --> 00:44:27,079
She felt guilty about it

807
00:44:27,880 --> 00:44:29,800
and kept pushing me to return to school

808
00:44:29,960 --> 00:44:30,880
and focus on studies.

809
00:44:32,320 --> 00:44:33,960
Were they together before?

810
00:44:35,559 --> 00:44:36,039
Yes.

811
00:44:38,159 --> 00:44:38,960
Xin used

812
00:44:38,960 --> 00:44:40,639
to attend a normal college in the city.

813
00:44:42,199 --> 00:44:43,199
Cha would bike

814
00:44:43,199 --> 00:44:44,360
to visit her every week.

815
00:44:44,840 --> 00:44:45,760
Riding a bicycle

816
00:44:46,760 --> 00:44:47,960
for five or six hours.

817
00:44:49,559 --> 00:44:50,559
But later,

818
00:44:52,320 --> 00:44:54,119
Xin thought Cha took the wrong path

819
00:44:54,920 --> 00:44:55,800
and was crooked,

820
00:44:58,960 --> 00:45:00,039
so they broke up.

821
00:45:06,079 --> 00:45:07,719
Cha isn't that bad.

822
00:45:08,639 --> 00:45:09,119
Right?

823
00:45:12,880 --> 00:45:13,840
He's a good person.

824
00:45:15,920 --> 00:45:17,440
He just never got proper schooling.

825
00:45:17,760 --> 00:45:18,760
He's uncultured,

826
00:45:20,039 --> 00:45:20,480
so he

827
00:45:20,480 --> 00:45:22,039
couldn't find decent work.

828
00:45:24,039 --> 00:45:26,360
He can only do what he knows how to do.

829
00:45:26,920 --> 00:45:27,519
Same with Rat.

830
00:45:29,079 --> 00:45:29,840
He's not bad.

831
00:45:33,400 --> 00:45:36,079
His dad was a murderer.

832
00:45:38,159 --> 00:45:39,480
When his dad got locked up,

833
00:45:39,920 --> 00:45:42,599
he and his mom
became outcasts in the village.

834
00:45:46,239 --> 00:45:48,400
His mom couldn't take the bullying

835
00:45:53,840 --> 00:45:54,840
and killed herself.

836
00:45:58,440 --> 00:45:59,239
As for Rat,

837
00:46:01,239 --> 00:46:03,360
he's lived feeling ashamed,

838
00:46:03,519 --> 00:46:05,039
like he's inferior to others,

839
00:46:06,079 --> 00:46:07,280
so he doesn't go to school.

840
00:46:07,760 --> 00:46:08,880
Just wandering around.

841
00:46:15,719 --> 00:46:18,159
Why are there
so many unfortunate people in the world?

842
00:46:21,880 --> 00:46:23,159
Living like weeds,

843
00:46:23,159 --> 00:46:24,760
easy to be crushed underfoot.

844
00:46:31,639 --> 00:46:32,920
You asked me before

845
00:46:36,480 --> 00:46:37,880
why I grabbed your knife.

846
00:46:42,280 --> 00:46:42,960
No reason.

847
00:46:44,760 --> 00:46:45,599
Just to help you.

848
00:46:46,239 --> 00:46:47,320
I wanted you to live.

849
00:46:50,639 --> 00:46:53,039
We hopeless folks

850
00:46:54,079 --> 00:46:54,960
are still hanging on.

851
00:46:56,760 --> 00:46:58,199
You did nothing wrong.

852
00:46:58,960 --> 00:47:00,360
And you've tried so hard.

853
00:47:02,239 --> 00:47:04,320
So you deserve to live well.

854
00:47:09,840 --> 00:47:10,519
Thank you

855
00:47:11,840 --> 00:47:13,159
for keeping me alive.

856
00:47:17,199 --> 00:47:18,599
When I was injured before,

857
00:47:20,199 --> 00:47:22,360
you kicked at my door.

858
00:47:24,960 --> 00:47:26,440
Seeing how worried you looked

859
00:47:28,719 --> 00:47:30,159
made me think

860
00:47:31,239 --> 00:47:33,239
this must be
what having family felt like.

861
00:47:41,199 --> 00:47:41,960
Ye Haitang.

862
00:47:46,719 --> 00:47:48,159
I want to be your family,

863
00:47:51,400 --> 00:47:52,360
if you let me.

864
00:47:56,280 --> 00:47:57,199
Let's live well.

865
00:48:03,840 --> 00:48:04,320
Okay.

866
00:48:05,880 --> 00:48:07,360
We'll live well.

867
00:48:08,159 --> 00:48:08,639
Okay.

868
00:48:10,320 --> 00:48:11,079
Live well.

869
00:48:13,559 --> 00:48:14,519
Live well.

870
00:48:35,480 --> 00:48:36,719
Millet porridge.

871
00:48:38,719 --> 00:48:39,480
Any else?

872
00:48:41,360 --> 00:48:42,159
Corn.

873
00:48:54,079 --> 00:48:54,840
Seek for.

874
00:48:55,599 --> 00:48:56,519
Both mean "seeking".

875
00:48:56,519 --> 00:48:57,400
What's the difference?

876
00:48:57,920 --> 00:48:58,840
"In search of"

877
00:48:58,840 --> 00:49:00,199
means seeking hard.

878
00:49:00,199 --> 00:49:02,000
It emphasizes the active effort.

879
00:49:02,280 --> 00:49:03,199
What follows it?

880
00:49:03,519 --> 00:49:05,320
In search of a job.

881
00:49:05,960 --> 00:49:07,320
Or what you all crave.

